a < \sigma < b
\int_0^\infty |f(x)|x^{\sigma - 1}\,dx < \infty
a < \Re(s) < b
F(s) = \int_0^\infty f(x)x^{s-1}\,dx
f(x) = \frac{1}{2 \pi i} \int_{\sigma - i\infty}^{\sigma + i\infty}F(s)x^{-s}\,ds
F
a < \Re(s) < b
\int_{\sigma - i \infty}^{\sigma + i \infty} |F(s)|\,ds<\infty
f(x) = \frac{1}{2 \pi i} \int_{\sigma - i\infty}^{\sigma + i\infty}F(s)x^{-s}\,ds
\int_0^\infty f(x)x^{s-1}\,dx = F(s)
\int_{\sigma - i \infty}^{\sigma + i \infty} |F(s)|\,ds<\infty\,\,\Rightarrow \,\,\int_0^\infty |f(x)|x^{\sigma - 1}\,dx < \infty
